!! Introduction
!!! Recognizing Jesus' Sovereignty and the Significance
You see two contrast for Peter. You see Peter at the highest and Peter at his lower.
This contrasting picture has to be deliberate.

Mark 1:1 has set out to show that Jesus is the Son of God. The only thing until Mark 8 has been demons that recognize Jesus as the Son of God.

Without understand who Christ is, we can't move forward to the Cross and understand its significance.

Peter is the mouth piece for the team but he is voicing the thoughts of the team. It is the reason when Peter is rebuked, Jesus turns to to see His disciples verse 33.

!!! Background of Peter
!!!! Peter's Father
Peter the Son of Jonah. Simon Bar-Jonah. Peter got his name from Christ. The Aramaic word is Cephas. 

Moses refers to God as a rock because He is unshakable, unchanging.

This is an interesting designation because of how fickle Peter is. Perhaps Peter was given this name as a sort of encouragement to what he will eventually become. We see Peter gain a bit of stability in the book of Acts.

!!!! Peter the Leader
Peter is only referred to Simon when he does what the flesh desires.
John ~MacArthur says "Peter is a person with a foot shaped mouth." Yet we see Peter as a leader of the twelve. Peter's name is most named among everyone.

No one is praised and blessed by Christ than Peter but also the harshest rebuke that Christ has ever given.

!!!! Peter's Companions
Mark 1:36; 1620

Peter was part of the inner circle. 
Jesus pinpoints Peter and picked on him when he was in the garden of Gethsemane.

This is Peter's life, what characterizes him. 

!!!! Peter Truly Loves the Lord.
Peter was a broken discouraged man after he denied Christ. He ran off weeping bitterly.
When Jesus came back, you see Peter jump into water to Christ.

In John 21, Jesus restores Him. After the Cross, Peter becomes genuinely consistent.

!!!! A Heart Changed
Peter was the one who spoke up and thousands heard the Lord.
His message was that God sent His Son and He was our messiah but you killed Him.

Peter was predicted to be mardered from John 21.
It has been said that Peter had to see his wife get crucified first and then him. Peter tells his wife that to remember the Lord. Then Peter got crucified upside down because he felt that he didn't want to dishonor Christ.

