Mark 8:27-30

!!!! Who Do You Say that I am?

Jesus is in Caesarea Philippi and talks with His disciples.
Here, Jesus asks his disciples, "Who do you say that I am?"

This question can only be answered by those who truly know Christ and follow Him.
Some people say John the Baptist others say Elijah. 

We've seen this before in Mark 6:14
Herod was terrified of John so he was convinced that it was John the Baptist. That opinion has permeated.

!!!! Not Just Good but God
Some of Jesus' disciple thought genuinely that Jesus was John the Baptist. Others say Jesus was a prophet because there has been hundreds of years of silence. So maybe to them, it wasn't a far fetched idea that maybe by the power of God, similar to Elijah's ministry, where John the Baptist rose from the dead.

